{\rtf1\ansi Monologue editing requires some things to keep in mind. Note the table on the far left. This table contains all the characters for the monologues. It contains the alphabet and what's this? Characters surrounded by "$", "#", "[" and "]"? \line\line \b$...$: \b0Entries surrounded by "$" will be ignored by the graphic preview. \line\line \b[...]: \b0Entries surrounded by hard brackets are entries that affect how the dialogue is displayed in-game. These will not have a graphical display as characters. The character [\\n] is special in that it won't show up as "[\\n]" when editing the text entries but shows up as a line break. \line\line \b#...#: \b0Will show a graphical value corresponding to it's index in the table file ... with the exception of "#Name#" which will show "LINK" instead. \line\line The table on the right is the gameÓ³ DTE table and is used for compression.}
